Association (TKSA) plans to conduct a Level One technical course early next month in Dar es Salaam. A week-long course will be conducted from March 7th to 12th in the city. According to the TKSA Chairman, Abdallah Nyoni, the preparation for the course is going on well and is in its final stages. Nyoni said during the course the participants will learn kabaddi rules, regulation and interpretation of the game, kabaddi venue’s preparation, practical on-field courses, signal use, decision-making and rules coordination (will focus on the intermediate referee decision making). Other’s topics in the training include the best kabaddi game management and good governance in the sport. The chairman added that those wishing to take part in the course are required to pay 70,000/- as a course fee. He said that all the payments will be made through the Bank of Baroda Account: 960101000081838 under the name of Buffalo Kabaddi sports Club. Nyoni stressed that conducting Kabaddi training is one of this year's strategies to promote the game. “We have good coaches and referees who will be used to conduct and oversee the development program of the game right from the Primary School level,” he said. Adding, he said the course is open for all stakeholders who are passionate about becoming games coaches and referees so as to push the kabaddi game forward. He said apart from the school programmes, TKSA has also set goals to spread the game by introducing it into the military institutions. However, from the beginning Nyoni said they plan to focus on the National Service Unit (JKT) and Tanzania Prisons departments for the early training so as to increase the number of clubs. He urged stakeholders to come forward in large numbers to attend the training as Kabaddi is one of the fast developing sports in the country.